<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>HUGO AWARD</strong></p>
<div class="code-block code-block-9">
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Awarded for the best science fiction or fantasy story of 40,000 words or more published in English or translated in the prior calendar year.</em></p>
<p><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250835000" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-132343 size-medium aligncenter" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-196x300.jpg" sizes="auto, (max-width: 196px) 100vw, 196px" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory.jpg 1613w" alt="Some Desperate Glory" width="196" height="300" data-attachment-id="132343" data-permalink="https://bookmarks.reviews/?attachment_id=132343" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory.jpg" data-orig-size="1613,2475" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Some Desperate Glory" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/12/Some-Desperate-Glory-667x1024.jpg" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781250835000" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Some Desperate Glory</em></a> by Emily Tesh</strong><br />
<strong>(Tor Books)</strong></p>
<p>“What begins as classic military space opera blossoms into something far more complex and interesting … The well-told story combines thrilling action with more thoughtful content, touching on such hot topics as AI, fascism and gender politics, and looks like another award winner.”</p>
<p style="text-align: right;">–Lisa Tuttle (<a href="https://www.theguardian.com/books/2023/apr/07/the-best-recent-science-fiction-and-fantasy-reviews-roundup" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Guardian</em></a>)</p>
</div>
<p><strong>Finalists:</strong></p>
